contentList.title: Big Girls Don't Cry

Meanwhile, our BGDC gang is gearing up for their final year in school with every intention of ruling the campus. Noor has her eyes on the School Captaincy while Ludo is chasing down the Sports Captaincy post. In this battle to save lives and heal others, the ones doing the fixing are the most broken.

contentList.title: Bogus Phone Operators

Scamsters from India impersonated IRS officials, swindling $50 million from Americans, especially targeting senior citizens, by instilling fear, and funneled the money back to India. The documentary exposes the modus operandi of these call center crimes as they continue to proliferate.

contentList.title: Strictly Street

The street food scenes in India are diverse to a maddening degree, and they evolve as quickly as the tastes of the people here do. Rohan Patoley is back, and this time around sniffs out the streets of this colourful subcontinent for all the new, exciting and lesser-known bites it has to offer.

contentList.title: Sweet Kaaram Coffee
contentList.summary: Created by Reshma Ghatala, Sweet Kaaram Coffee is a slice of life series. Sundari, a 70-year-old quirky, free-spirited woman, contemplates reaching out to a distant source of happiness after her husband passes away. She fears that her caring son Rajaratnam, with the best of intentions, might confine and suffocate her like her husband did. She looks out for an avenue to further her escape plan and suggests it to the other two women when the opportunity arises.

contentList.title: Pachinko

contentList.title: Bambai Meri Jaan
contentList.summary: Bambai Meri Jaan, the series chronicles the rise of organised crime in post-independent India. Spanning over six decades, ‘Bambai Meri Jaan’ tells the story of an honest cop, who in his quest to clean the mean streets of Bombay puts everything on the line including that he wants to protect the most, his family. It’s a saga of what has plagued man since eternity, absolute power. It’s an ode to the city of Bombay told through the eyes of a young boy from the streets of Dongri. A policeman’s son, who goes on to become a fugitive from law to hide in Dubai, creating one of the world’s largest crime syndicate that will eventually take him down a path of revenge and self destruction.
